Washima (, Washima-mura?) was a village located in Sant District, Niigata, Japan. As of 2003, the village had an estimated population of 4,814 and a density of 151.10 persons per km. The total area was 31.86km. On January 1, 2006 Washima, along with the towns of Teradomari and Yoita, all from Sant District, and the city of Tochio, was merged into the expanded city of Nagaoka. 
